parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake violently when braking, especially at high speeds or when going downhill, which can lead to loss of control and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates when braking
the steering wheel shakes
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the rotors overheat
the vehicle requires frequent replacement of rotors and brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive dimming of the instrument panel can cause the gauges to become unreadable, creating a hazardous condition for drivers, passengers, and other vehicles on the road.
symptoms: The instrument panel becomes extremely dark
making it difficult or impossible to read the gauges
especially in sunny conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle lunges forward and backward without warning
often accompanied by sudden and unexpected acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Wear of Tires and Brake Rotors
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear of tires and brake rotors can lead to reduced vehicle safety, increased stopping distances, and a higher risk of accidents. Additionally, frequent replacements can result in increased maintenance costs.
symptoms: Tires showing excessive wear
uneven tire wear
reduced tire tread depth
brake rotors requiring frequent resurfacing or replacement
brake pads wearing out quickly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may accelerate unexpectedly, making it difficult for the driver to stop or maintain control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
the vehicle surges forward without pressing the accelerator
the vehicle fails to slow down or stop when the brake pedal is pressed
the engine RPM increases unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty accelerator pedal position sensor can cause unintended acceleration, making it difficult for the driver to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
the vehicle surges forward without pressing the accelerator
the vehicle fails to slow down or stop when the brake pedal is pressed
the engine RPM increases unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the Electronic Throttle Control (ETC) system can cause unintended acceleration, making it difficult for the driver to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
the vehicle surges forward without pressing the accelerator
the vehicle fails to slow down or stop when the brake pedal is pressed
the engine RPM increases unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the steering wheel to shake or vibrate when braking, especially at high speeds, which can lead to a loss of control and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Steering wheel shakes or vibrates when braking
especially at high speeds (above 40 mph)
uneven brake pedal feel
spongy brake pedal
or a grinding noise when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear and discoloration of the driver's seat can lead to discomfort and distraction while driving, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Separation of stitching on the seat
discoloration of the seat material
uneven wear on the seat cushion or backrest.
